text: Novyye Tatyshly () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Novotatyshlinsky Selsoviet, Tatyshlinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 550 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 10 km from Verkhniye Tatyshly. == References == Category:Rural localities in Tatyshlinsky District
title: Novyye Tatyshly
